<TITLE> Cyclone Laila weakens </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 21 (bdnews24.com)  The cyclonic storm Laila moved slightly northwards and weakened into a cyclonic storm over costal areas of north east Andhra Pradesh of India the Meteorological Department said in special bulletin on early Friday. Laila is likely to weaken gradually and move further in a northerly direction. Under it's influence a deep convection is taking place over the north Bay of Bengal and adjoining coastal areas of Bangladesh causing squally weather and rough seas. Maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazaar and Mongla are advised to keep local cautionary signal number three hoisted. All fishing boats and trawlers over north Bay have been advised to remain in shelter until further notice
